# Roadmap Workflow

The build plan lives in `ROADMAP.md` (one task per day, 6 phases).

When the user says "day N" (or uses the day-runner skill):

1. Read ONLY the Day N entry in `ROADMAP.md` — not the whole file's phases
2. Restate the task in one sentence; list the files you will touch (usually 1–3)
3. Make the edits per token-discipline rules
4. Verify: run the check named in the task (curl/browser), report pass or fail honestly
5. Stop. Commit message format: `day-N: <task name>`. Do not start Day N+1

Guardrails:

- Days 4–10 are security work: never weaken auth to "make tests pass";
  401 on a protected route is the desired outcome
- Never print or commit real secrets; reference `.env` keys by name only
- If a task depends on an unfinished earlier day, say so and stop instead of improvising
